results.name: Jordan 12 Retro Royalty Taxi (PS)
results.story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 12 Retro PS ‘Royalty’ brings back the distinctive two-tone color blocking of the OG ‘Taxi’ colorway. Radiating stitched lines distinguish the white tumbled leather upper, fortified with black lizard-textured overlays and accented with metallic gold eyelets. Atop the tongue, matching gold accents take the form of a Jumpman icon and embroidered ‘Two 3’ branding. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a Phylon midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro Where the Wild Things Are (PS)
results.story: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 4 PS ‘Wild Things’ adds warm fleece construction to the padded collar and tongue, the latter accented with an embroidered Jumpman icon. The rest of the upper is built with tan leather and a quartet of color-popped eyelets in neon green, pink, blue and red. A second Jumpman logo embellishes a molded heel panel in dark beige. The sneaker sits on a two-tone foam midsole, supported by an outsole built with gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro Pine Green (PS)
results.story: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 3 Retro PS ‘Pine Green’ adds verdant color-popped accents to the hardwood stalwart that originally launched in 1988. The upper is constructed from smooth black nubuck with signature elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting hits of Pine Green appear on the eyelets, perforated collar and the Jumpman icon embroidered on the tongue. A second Jumpman logo is embossed on the back heel. The sneaker rests on a two-tone foam midsole, supported underfoot by a durable grey rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 13 Retro White Obsidian Powder Blue (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS ‘Obsidian’ combines OG-style color blocking with a familiar palette and traditional materials. They include a navy leather base, tonal suede paneling and large stitched leather overlays in a pristine shade of white. The 13’s signature holographic emblem graces the lateral collar, while a Jumpman icon is embroidered in powder blue atop the tongue. The latter hue is repeated on the panther paw outsole, equipped with herringbone-tread rubber pods for game-ready traction.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro Lightning (2021) (PS)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS ‘Lightning’ resurrects an immensely popular colorway originally released in 2006. Built for little kids, this pair carries an upper crafted from smooth nubuck in a vibrant yellow hue. The 4’s signature wings are rendered in a dark grey finish, while contrasting black accents land on the eyelets and the decorative netting that covers the quarter panel and throat. Jumpman branding adorns the tongue and heel overlay. The mid-top rides on a white foam midsole and grey rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 12 Retro Utility (PS)
results.story: Constructed for little kids, the Jordan 12 Utility PS ‘Grind’ pairs a subdued palette with a pragmatic design approach. Black tumbled leather is utilized on the upper, featuring radiating stitched lines and tonal overlays in smooth nubuck. Atop the ballistic mesh tongue, a crimson Jumpman offers a contrasting burst of color. The sneaker is mounted on a matching black Phylon midsole and speckled rubber outsole made with 3% Nike Grind, a catchall term that refers to recycled scrap materials — including rubber, foam, leather and textiles — sourced from unused manufacturing scraps and end-of-life shoes.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Pollen (PS)
results.story: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Pollen’ is highlighted by a two-tone design reminiscent of the OG ‘Iowa’ Dunk High from 1985. The leather upper pairs a black base with contrasting overlays in Pollen yellow. A woven Nike tongue tag adorns the lightly padded nylon tongue, while a classic Wings logo is imprinted in black on the lateral collar. The high-top is mounted on a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring crisp white sidewalls and a yellow rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 12 Retro Twist (PS)
results.story: Offered in little kid sizing, the Air Jordan 12 Retro PS ‘Twist’ brings back an OG-inspired palette initially employed on the ‘Cherry’ colorway from 1997. The mid-top makes use of a white tumbled leather upper with radiating stitched lines, tonal lizard-textured overlays and molded upper eyelets in University Red. Jumpman branding makes its way to the tongue and woven heel tab, which also features a Jordan wordmark in block lettering. The sneaker rides on a cushy foam midsole, supported by a herringbone-traction rubber pods under the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro Racer Blue (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 3 Retro PS ‘Racer Blue’ features classic color blocking on the silhouette that introduced elephant print to the Jordan franchise. Rendered in a dark grey finish, the distinctive crackle pattern appears on the sneaker’s forefoot and heel overlays, while the rest of the upper is executed in white tumbled leather. Contrasting royal blue accents make their way to eyelets, collar and midsole, as well as Jumpman branding hits atop the tongue and heel.

results.name: Jordan 13 Retro Low Very Berry (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 13 Retro Low PS ‘Very Berry’ combines black paneling in leather and synthetic suede with dimpled leather overlays in a crimson finish. The same red hue is applied to the Jumpman branding hits that decorate the tongue and lateral collar. The low-top silhouette rides on a two-tone white and black midsole, supported by a distinctive panther paw outsole equipped with herringbone rubber traction pods for reliable grip.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro White Oreo (2021) (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS ‘White Oreo’ presents a neutral colorway of Tinker Hatfield’s vintage design from 1989. The sneaker carries a white leather upper with subtle hits of Tech Grey on the eyelets, interior lining and speckled foam midsole, absent the visible Air sole unit of the shoe’s full-sized counterpart. Matching grey Jumpman branding on the heel is contrasted by a scarlet Jumpman icon atop the tongue, delivering the lone pop of color.

results.name: Jordan 3 Retro A Ma Maniére (PS)
results.story: Designed in partnership with James Whitner’s luxury boutique, the A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 3 Retro SP PS ‘Raised By Women’ showcases a premium build crafted for little kids. Whitner opted for the 3 as it was the first Jordan model that his mother bought for him, and its subtle design is inspired by and made for the women in his life. The upper is constructed from tumbled white leather with grey suede overlays at the toe and heel. Grey quilted satin lines the collar and tongue, featuring a Jumpman on the right shoe and A Ma Maniére branding on the left. ‘Nike Air’ is embossed on the yellowed heel tab. The same vintage finish is applied to the foam midsole, contrasted by violet detailing that wraps around the back heel.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Electric Green (PS)
results.story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 6 Retro PS ‘Electric Green’ features the same color blocking and materials found on the venerable ‘Infrared’ colorway, which Michael Jordan was wearing on court when he captured his first ever NBA championship. The layered upper is constructed from black nubuck with breathable perforations and a spoiler-like heel tab accented with bright green detailing. The fluorescent hue is repeated on the midsole, as well as the Jumpman logo that adorns the tongue and sockliner. An additional Jumpman is embroidered in tonal fashion on the back heel.

results.name: Jordan 11 Retro Low Legend Blue (PS)
results.story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low PS ‘Legend Blue’ brings back an OG 1996 colorway in low-top form. The upper is constructed from white leather with a tonal patent leather mudguard and powder blue accents inspired by MJ’s alma mater. On the insole, a Jumpman icon is joined by a ‘25’ graphic that marks the shoe’s silver anniversary. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length Phylon midsole, reinforced underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Jordan 1 Retro High Court Purple (PS) (2021)
results.story: Offered in little kids sizing, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Court Purple’ features a simplistic two-tone design that recalls the OG ‘Metallic Purple’ colorway from 1986. The high-top carries a white tumbled leather upper with contrasting violet accents on the glossy Swoosh, collar and satin-lined interior. The same hue is utilized on the Wings logo stamped on the lateral collar flap and the woven Nike tag that decorates the leather tongue.

results.name: Jordan 13 Retro Gym Red Flint Grey (PS)
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 13 Retro PS ‘Red Flint’ features traditional color blocking redolent of the shoe’s OG ‘Flint’ colorway from 1998. The mid-top makes use of the same blend of white leather and grey synthetic suede used on the original, contrasted by Gym Red detailing in lieu of the older shoe’s blue accents. The crimson hits of color land on the sneaker’s reflective mesh overlays, interior tongue and collar lining. A black Jumpman icon atop the tongue is complemented by a second Jumpman logo on the distinctive panther paw outsole.

results.name: Jordan 6 Retro Travis Scott British Khaki (PS)
results.story: Built for little kids, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro PS ‘British Khaki’ delivers a refined take on the classic mid-top. Soft suede in a dark tan finish makes up the composition of the upper, equipped with a button stash pocket on the lateral collar and a zippered pouch on the medial side. A Jumpman icon in Bright Crimson stands out on the canvas tongue, matched by Nike Air and Cactus Jack logos on the heel of the left and right shoe. They’re joined by the Houston rapper’s personal branding hits on the medial-side midsole and semi-translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan 4 Retro University Blue (PS)
results.story: Constructed for little kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro PS ‘University Blue’ updates the iconic silhouette with a UNC-inspired palette and a smooth suede build. As a callback to the OG ‘White Cement’ colorway, speckled grey detailing is applied to the TPU wings, Air-infused foam midsole and Jumpman branded heel patch. A second Jumpman can be found on the woven jock tag atop the tongue, modeled after the labeling used on vintage Nike basketball jerseys.
